{{Ill|Kamo no Okimi|ja|鴨王 (上古)}} ([[Okimi]] of the [[Kamo clan]]) was the son of [[Kotoshironushi]] and [[Tamakushi-hime]], and brother of [[Himetataraisuzu-hime]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kamo no Ōkimi • . A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史 |url=https://historyofjapan.co.uk/wiki/kamo-no-okimi/ |access-date=2023-03-20 |website=. A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史 |language=en-GB}}</ref> He was an ancestor of the [[Kamo clan]], and by extension through {{Nihongo|{{ill|Ōtataneko|ja|大田田根子命}}|太田田根子}} the [[Miwa clan]].

He was the father of {{Ill|Nunasokonakatsu-hime|ja|渟名底仲媛}}<ref name=":9">Anston, p. 143 (Vol. 1)</ref> and thus the grandfather of [[Emperor Itoku]].<ref name="Varley 892">{{cite book |author=[[H. Paul Varley|Varley, H. Paul.]] |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tVv6OAAACAAJ |title=Jinnō Shōtōki: A Chronicle of Gods and Sovereigns |publisher=Columbia University Press |year=1980 |isbn=9780231049405 |page=89}}</ref>




